
## Configuration Files

The installer creates temporary configuration files:
- `/tmp/gentoo-install-config` - Main installation configuration
- `/tmp/gentoo-disk-config` - Disk and partitioning configuration
- `/tmp/gentoo-filesystem-config` - Filesystem configuration
- `/tmp/gentoo-encryption-config` - Encryption configuration
- `/tmp/gentoo-fstab` - Generated fstab file

## Requirements

- Gentoo Linux (source-based distribution)
- Root access
- Internet connection for downloading stage tarballs
- Minimum 2GB RAM (for kernel compilation)
- Sufficient disk space (recommended 20GB+)

## Supported Disk Layouts

### Simple Layout
- Boot partition (512MB)
- Root partition (remaining space)

### Advanced Layout
- EFI System Partition (512MB)
- Boot partition (512MB)
- Swap partition (2GB or more)
- Root partition (remaining space)
- Optional separate /home and /var partitions

### Encrypted Layout
- EFI System Partition (unencrypted or encrypted)
- Boot partition (optionally encrypted)
- Root partition (LUKS encrypted)

### RAID Layout
- Multiple disks in RAID arrays
- Separate RAID arrays for boot and root
- Hardware or software RAID support

## Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

1. **Missing dependencies**: Run `make install-deps`
2. **Dialog not found**: Install with `emerge sys-apps/dialog`
3. **Insufficient disk space**: Ensure adequate free space (20GB+)
4. **Network issues**: Verify internet connection for downloading

### Log Files

The installer creates log files in `/tmp/`:
- `gentoo-install.log` - Main installation log
- Partitioning and formatting logs
- Installation progress logs

### Getting Help

- Gentoo Handbook: https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Handbook
- Installation Guide: https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Installation_guide
- Support Forums: https://forums.gentoo.org/

## Safety Notes

⚠️ **WARNING**: This installer will partition and format disks. All data on selected disks will be lost!

- Always backup important data before using this installer
- Verify disk selection carefully
- Test on virtual machines before real hardware
- Review configuration before executing installation

